data.chText: 旁观者站在一定的距离之外，以示尊敬。
data.enText: The onlookers stood at a respectful distance.

data.chText: 我们从小就学会了尊重权威。
data.enText: We were brought up to be respectful of authority.

simple_means.memory_skill: re 一再 + spect 看 + ful …的，respect的形容词 → 充满敬意的

ex.chText: 在学生眼里，他是一位勤勉可敬的老师。
ex.enText: According to his students, he is a hard-working and respectable teacher.

synonyms.bx: 指因品质、行为等高尚而应该得到他人尊敬的。

ex.chText: 他是过去10年中最受尊敬的篮球运动员之一。
ex.enText: He's one of the most respected basketball players in the last decade.

ex.chText: 她是一位广受尊敬的评论员。
ex.enText: She was a widely respected commentator.

synonyms.bx: 指因取得的成就而受人敬重的。

ex.chText: 他们安静地站着，以示尊敬。
他一向尊重女儿的独立。
ex.enText: He was always respectful of his daughter's independence.

synonyms.bx: 指对某人或某事物表示尊敬或敬意的。

value.def: If you are respectful, you show respect for someone.

example.ex: He was always so polite and respectful...
example.tran: 他总是彬彬有礼，尊敬他人。

example.ex: The children in our family are always respectful to their elders...
example.tran: 我们家的孩子对长辈总是恭恭敬敬的。

example.ex: The patient has the right to considerate and respectful care.
example.tran: 病人有权得到周到而礼貌的照顾。

value.tran: 尊重人的;有礼貌的;恭敬的

example.ex: 'You are an artist,' she said respectfully.
example.tran: “您是一位艺术家，”她毕恭毕敬地说。
